1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,806
You holding up okay?

2
00:00:02,450 --> 00:00:03,986
Dying of boredom yet?

3
00:00:03,986 --> 00:00:05,300
BRIDGETTE:
Nuh-uh.

4
00:00:05,895 --> 00:00:07,214
Just 15 more minutes.

5
00:00:07,214 --> 00:00:09,124
Then we'll meet Mom
and the girls by the shoe department,

6
00:00:09,124 --> 00:00:10,758
and then we'll go
to the movie, okay?

7
00:00:10,758 --> 00:00:13,849
Okay, but what are
you buying socks for?

8
00:00:13,849 --> 00:00:15,858
Don't you have plenty
of socks at home?

9
00:00:15,858 --> 00:00:18,130
It's not
like you're still growing.

10
00:00:18,130 --> 00:00:20,521
Well, you know,over time, they wear out.

11
00:00:20,521 --> 00:00:23,327
And sometimes
the dryer eats them.

12
00:00:23,327 --> 00:00:26,545
You mean we have a dryer
that eats things?

13
00:00:26,545 --> 00:00:27,737
Huh?

14
00:00:28,442 --> 00:00:32,933
Uh, no, no, it's just sometimes
things get lost in there.Socks mostly.

15
00:00:32,933 --> 00:00:35,840
It's not like
it actually eats anything.

16
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:38,264
Stay here for just one second, baby.

17
00:00:38,264 --> 00:00:40,686
I just want to ask
this salesman something.

18
00:00:40,686 --> 00:00:42,522
Excuse me, uh,

19
00:00:42,522 --> 00:00:44,107
I'm looking for
these in the crew.

20
00:00:44,107 --> 00:00:45,215
I'll be right over, sir.

21
00:00:45,215 --> 00:00:45,986
Thank you.

22
00:00:51,057 --> 00:00:51,886
Bridgette?

23
00:00:53,353 --> 00:00:54,311
Bridgette?!

24
00:00:54,692 --> 00:00:57,024
Bridgette.

25
00:00:59,531 --> 00:01:00,816
Bridge?

26
00:01:02,287 --> 00:01:03,774
Bridge!

27
00:01:06,854 --> 00:01:09,570
Bridge!Bridgette Dubois?!

28
00:01:27,238 --> 00:01:30,141
ALLISON:
Hey. It's 4:00 in the morning.

29
00:01:30,141 --> 00:01:31,032
What are you doing up?

30
00:01:31,032 --> 00:01:34,070
Hey. It's 4:00 in the morning.

31
00:01:34,070 --> 00:01:35,401
What are you doing out?

32
00:01:36,374 --> 00:01:38,033
LISON:
What can I tell you.
People are terrified.

33
00:01:38,033 --> 00:01:40,316
Every time
a red-headed woman who lives alone

34
00:01:40,316 --> 00:01:42,475
hears the wind jangling
a loose screen,

35
00:01:42,475 --> 00:01:45,213
she thinks she's got
a close encounter with the Phoenix Phantom.

36
00:01:45,213 --> 00:01:46,279
And...?

37
00:01:47,476 --> 00:01:48,625
Not tonight.

38
00:01:50,128 --> 00:01:52,866
Not the three women
that I sat with,thankfully,

39
00:01:52,866 --> 00:01:56,492
although I did have the distinct honor
of watching 

40
00:01:56,492 --> 00:01:59,484
the coroner pull the body
of the first victim

41
00:01:59,484 --> 00:02:02,346
out of a Dumpster behind
a gentleman's club.

42
00:02:03,343 --> 00:02:04,904
Ah...

43
00:02:05,404 --> 00:02:06,479
well...

44
00:02:08,587 --> 00:02:13,324
Okay, can you reset the alarm
after you get up at 6:30

45
00:02:13,324 --> 00:02:14,256
for me at noon?

46
00:02:14,256 --> 00:02:17,728
Absolutely. Wouldn't want to be
late making the kids breakfast,

47
00:02:17,728 --> 00:02:19,926
getting them dressed,
taking them to school,

48
00:02:19,926 --> 00:02:23,533
making them dinner or helping them out
with their homework.

49
00:02:23,533 --> 00:02:24,329
I'm sorry.

50
00:02:24,329 --> 00:02:26,288
I'm... I know you are.

51
00:02:26,288 --> 00:02:27,757
I-I'm sorry.

52
00:02:29,294 --> 00:02:30,759
People are dying.You're trying to help.

53
00:02:30,759 --> 00:02:32,406
I get it. I do.
It's just...

54
00:02:33,303 --> 00:02:35,134
It's... it's unfair.

55
00:02:38,208 --> 00:02:41,962
I can fix this.I swear.

56
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:51,315
Oh... now let's just hope

57
00:02:51,315 --> 00:02:52,383
that between now and noon,

58
00:02:52,383 --> 00:02:54,873
I don't have any scary dreams
that wake me up.

59
00:02:55,821 --> 00:02:57,637
Well, I don't think
you need to worry
about that.

60
00:02:57,637 --> 00:03:00,375
I already did that
for you, too.

61
00:03:55,538 --> 00:03:56,895
I'm sorry.

62
00:03:56,895 --> 00:03:59,904
Mommy always puts her hand
on the top of my head so the hair doesn't pull.

63
00:03:59,904 --> 00:04:01,077
Yeah, I'm sure she does.

64
00:04:01,356 --> 00:04:02,777
...was discovered
yesterday evening

65
00:04:02,777 --> 00:04:04,054
in a Dumpster outside

66
00:04:04,054 --> 00:04:04,964
the Fantasy Lounge.

67
00:04:04,964 --> 00:04:06,052
Bridge... hey, hey.Bridge, 

68
00:04:06,052 --> 00:04:07,701
Bridge...turn that off, will you?

69
00:04:07,701 --> 00:04:10,927
...apparent abduction three
nights ago of Darlene Denise.

70
00:04:10,927 --> 00:04:11,792
Another redhead...

71
00:04:12,673 --> 00:04:14,303
She's eating cookies.

72
00:04:14,303 --> 00:04:15,436
Nuh-uh!

73
00:04:15,436 --> 00:04:16,865
You know what? I don't care.

74
00:04:16,865 --> 00:04:18,476
Everybody get their stuff
together.

75
00:04:18,476 --> 00:04:19,983
Let's get this show
on the road.

76
00:04:19,983 --> 00:04:21,725
Mommy's not taking us
again today?

77
00:04:21,725 --> 00:04:23,294
Ariel, look around.Do you see Mommy?

78
00:04:25,789 --> 00:04:27,979
Come on.
This isn't new.Mommy worked late,

79
00:04:27,979 --> 00:04:29,311
so Mommy's sleeping in.

80
00:04:33,197 --> 00:04:34,258
Good night.

81
00:04:43,312 --> 00:04:44,467
WOMAN:
Must be the night shift.

82
00:04:44,467 --> 00:04:45,935
He's waiting for you.

83
00:04:45,935 --> 00:04:47,806
Have a nice evening.

84
00:04:47,806 --> 00:04:48,658
Are you kidding?

85
00:04:48,658 --> 00:04:49,748
I'm going home
and rinsing out

86
00:04:49,748 --> 00:04:51,328
the little bit of red
I have left in my hair.

87
00:04:56,662 --> 00:04:57,955
Knock, knock.

88
00:04:57,955 --> 00:04:59,649
Tell me you had a dream.

89
00:04:59,649 --> 00:05:00,662
I had a dream.

90
00:05:00,662 --> 00:05:02,161
I was having dinner
with my family.

91
00:05:02,161 --> 00:05:03,225
Keep dreaming.

92
00:05:03,225 --> 00:05:05,942
We had 11 calls last night
from women convinced
the Phantom

93
00:05:05,942 --> 00:05:07,732
was trying to break
into their homes
or apartments

94
00:05:07,732 --> 00:05:09,622
from virtually every precinct
in the city.

95
00:05:09,622 --> 00:05:11,689
We've still got guys out
in the field running them down.

96
00:05:11,689 --> 00:05:14,653
Allison and I interviewed
three of them ourselves.

97
00:05:14,653 --> 00:05:15,367
And...?

98
00:05:15,367 --> 00:05:17,595
And two of them were genuinely frightened

99
00:05:17,595 --> 00:05:18,963
although without cause.

100
00:05:19,117 --> 00:05:20,704
The other one, she just wanted

101
00:05:20,704 --> 00:05:22,368
some attention
from her boyfriend.

102
00:05:22,368 --> 00:05:23,206
Uh-huh.

103
00:05:23,206 --> 00:05:24,990
All together, since
the second disappearance,

104
00:05:24,990 --> 00:05:26,496
we've had over 1,400 calls,

105
00:05:26,496 --> 00:05:29,460
tips, supposed sightings,
even six confessions.

106
00:05:30,459 --> 00:05:33,379
What's the "want"?
What's the "goal"?

107
00:05:33,379 --> 00:05:34,896
I mean, it can't
just be about red hair.

108
00:05:34,988 --> 00:05:37,080
Whoever did it,they know how
to break and enter.

109
00:05:37,087 --> 00:05:38,516
Places are clean as a whistle.

110
00:05:39,156 --> 00:05:42,511
These abductions are planned
and extremely well-thought-out.

111
00:05:42,511 --> 00:05:43,869
They're not random.

112
00:05:45,030 --> 00:05:45,984
Excuse me.

113
00:05:49,311 --> 00:05:50,360
It's home.

114
00:05:50,839 --> 00:05:51,833
Hello?

115
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:53,771
Hi, baby.

116
00:05:53,771 --> 00:05:55,159
Just a second.

117
00:05:55,159 --> 00:05:56,473
It's my oldest.

118
00:05:57,811 --> 00:05:58,725
Scanlon.

119
00:05:59,425 --> 00:06:00,820
Ariel, everything okay?

120
00:06:00,820 --> 00:06:03,234
Yeah. I was just wondering

121
00:06:03,234 --> 00:06:04,234
if you knew yet.

122
00:06:04,234 --> 00:06:05,574
Knew what?

123
00:06:05,574 --> 00:06:07,038
About tomorrow.

124
00:06:07,038 --> 00:06:08,711
Horseback riding.

125
00:06:10,784 --> 00:06:13,622
It would just be a lot more fun
if you could go, too.

126
00:06:14,119 --> 00:06:15,954
You know what?
Let me talk to my boss.

127
00:06:15,954 --> 00:06:17,520
See what I can do, okay?

128
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:18,707
I'll call you back, baby.

129
00:06:18,707 --> 00:06:19,462
Bye.

130
00:06:21,559 --> 00:06:22,703
I have a problem.

131
00:06:22,703 --> 00:06:25,072
I mean, I don't
mind working

132
00:06:25,072 --> 00:06:26,471
as a human lie detector,

133
00:06:26,471 --> 00:06:29,293
but it's been four nights
in a row now,

134
00:06:29,293 --> 00:06:31,712
and, frankly, my family
is starting to lose it.

135
00:06:32,769 --> 00:06:34,821
Is there any way I could take
a pass tonight?

136
00:06:35,705 --> 00:06:37,034
We just got a call.

137
00:06:37,104 --> 00:06:38,568
Apparently he's struck again.

138
00:06:45,302 --> 00:06:46,756
SCANLON:
You're awfully
quiet tonight.

139
00:06:46,756 --> 00:06:49,344
Hmm. Count your blessings.

140
00:06:49,344 --> 00:06:50,910
Sounds like a dare.

141
00:06:50,910 --> 00:06:52,549
Don't mind me.

142
00:06:52,549 --> 00:06:54,365
I'm just frustrated,
that's all.

143
00:06:55,223 --> 00:06:56,706
What are you frustrated about?

144
00:06:56,706 --> 00:06:57,889
That I'm here,

145
00:06:57,889 --> 00:06:59,900
that everyone's frustrated
with me.

146
00:07:00,497 --> 00:07:02,279
There's nothing I can do
about it.

147
00:07:02,279 --> 00:07:04,649
I'm guessing we're talking
about the home front, 'cause...

148
00:07:04,649 --> 00:07:06,597
no around here
is frustrated with you.

149
00:07:07,547 --> 00:07:09,962
Look, I'll make
you a deal.

150
00:07:09,962 --> 00:07:11,813
Let's just check out
this crime scene.

151
00:07:11,813 --> 00:07:12,946
It'll take all of half an hour.

152
00:07:12,946 --> 00:07:14,727
If nothing happens for you,then we'll call it a night.

153
00:07:15,149 --> 00:07:16,829
No home visits, no interviews.

154
00:07:16,829 --> 00:07:18,725
You'll be back at your car
by 10:00.Home by 11:00.

155
00:07:18,725 --> 00:07:19,554
How does
that sound?

156
00:07:19,589 --> 00:07:21,650
That sounds fantastic.

157
00:07:23,541 --> 00:07:24,664
God, I'm nice.

158
00:07:29,554 --> 00:07:31,055
MAN:
'Evening.

159
00:07:31,421 --> 00:07:33,735
That it is.
Who have we got here?

160
00:07:33,735 --> 00:07:35,788
The mother had been calling
for two days,

161
00:07:35,788 --> 00:07:37,332
saying she was trying
to reach her child.

162
00:07:37,332 --> 00:07:38,757
We finally got over here.

163
00:07:38,757 --> 00:07:39,960
Landlord let us in.

164
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:41,390
Seems to fit
the pattern.

165
00:07:41,390 --> 00:07:43,418
The victim appears
to have been roused from sleep.

166
00:07:43,418 --> 00:07:45,683
Haven't found
any blood or DNA just yet.

167
00:07:45,683 --> 00:07:47,299
No signs of a struggle.

168
00:07:47,299 --> 00:07:49,791
Redhead?
Of course.

169
00:07:49,791 --> 00:07:50,973
Can I see
the bedroom?

170
00:07:50,973 --> 00:07:52,689
SCANLON:
This is Allison Dubois.

171
00:07:52,689 --> 00:07:53,639
She's with the D.A.

172
00:07:54,637 --> 00:07:56,044
Find anything?

173
00:08:12,843 --> 00:08:13,843
Uh...

174
00:08:17,596 --> 00:08:19,623
Well, then, it's unanimous.

175
00:08:19,623 --> 00:08:22,388
The crime scene techs found
some nothing in the kitchen.

176
00:08:22,388 --> 00:08:23,993
That led them in here

177
00:08:23,993 --> 00:08:25,137
where they found
a little more nothing.

178
00:08:25,137 --> 00:08:27,627
Now they're checking
the perimeter which,

179
00:08:27,627 --> 00:08:29,016
if everything goes
according to pattern,

180
00:08:29,016 --> 00:08:30,182
will yield absolutely nothing.

181
00:08:32,096 --> 00:08:32,852
Hey, honey.

182
00:08:32,852 --> 00:08:34,607
Hang on a sec.

183
00:08:34,607 --> 00:08:36,263
We'll be out of here in 15.

184
00:08:37,189 --> 00:08:38,323
I'll be back.

185
00:08:40,379 --> 00:08:43,790
Hey, eldest child, good news.

186
00:08:43,790 --> 00:08:45,690
Mommy's leaving work shortly,
which means...

187
00:08:45,690 --> 00:08:49,475
I'll be going horseback riding
with you!

188
00:08:50,764 --> 00:08:54,205
Yes. Tell Daddy
I should be home by 11:00.

189
00:08:55,741 --> 00:08:56,836
Sure, put him on.

190
00:08:56,836 --> 00:08:59,775
MAN:
We're looking
for Isaiah, men.

191
00:08:59,775 --> 00:09:00,977
Find me Isaiah.

192
00:09:07,843 --> 00:09:09,150
Hello.

193
00:09:11,423 --> 00:09:13,511
I think
I might've
found it.

194
00:09:13,511 --> 00:09:15,490
I think it's on this mirror.

195
00:09:17,139 --> 00:09:19,165
I'm sorry, sir
but I just don't see it.

196
00:09:19,041 --> 00:09:19,885
<i>JOE ( over phone ):
Allison?</i>

197
00:09:20,534 --> 00:09:22,331
He did it with his
finger. Come here.

198
00:09:22,331 --> 00:09:23,700
JOE:
Allison?

199
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:25,463
Joe, I gotta call you back.

200
00:09:26,087 --> 00:09:27,863
You still don't
see it, do you?

201
00:09:29,380 --> 00:09:30,974
Let me show you
something.

202
00:09:38,215 --> 00:09:39,289
There we go.

203
00:09:41,891 --> 00:09:43,656
There it is.

204
00:09:44,735 --> 00:09:47,808
Isaiah 14:21.

205
00:09:48,797 --> 00:09:49,994
Damn it!

206
00:09:51,044 --> 00:09:52,158
I see him.

207
00:09:57,094 --> 00:09:58,600
All right.

208
00:09:58,760 --> 00:09:59,918
SCANLON:
You still on the phone?

209
00:10:01,263 --> 00:10:04,558
Allison... you ready
to get out of here?

210
00:10:09,183 --> 00:10:11,655
I think he left us a message.

211
00:10:11,655 --> 00:10:12,509
Who are you talking about?

212
00:10:12,509 --> 00:10:13,780
I didn't get anything
in the bedroom

213
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:15,247
because it didn't happen
in the bedroom.

214
00:10:15,247 --> 00:10:16,037
It happened in here.

215
00:10:18,083 --> 00:10:19,709
Whoa,
whoa,
whoa.

216
00:10:19,709 --> 00:10:21,215
There may be evidence in there.You probably
shouldn't...

217
00:10:21,215 --> 00:10:22,404
Look at the mirror.

218
00:10:24,167 --> 00:10:25,967
What is that?

219
00:10:28,506 --> 00:10:30,696
It's a message.It's a piece of scripture.

220
00:10:30,764 --> 00:10:33,281
Isaiah 14:21.

221
00:10:50,830 --> 00:10:52,709
I am not a toy.

222
00:10:52,709 --> 00:10:54,794
I'm not a thing.

223
00:10:54,794 --> 00:10:56,320
You're hung up on me.

224
00:10:57,503 --> 00:10:59,314
You can't just
start kissing me

225
00:10:59,314 --> 00:11:01,144
and expect everything
to be all right.

226
00:11:04,373 --> 00:11:05,995
Boy, you give up easily.

227
00:11:05,995 --> 00:11:12,571
Wow. Actually home
before midnight.

228
00:11:12,571 --> 00:11:14,057
You talking to me, toy?

229
00:11:14,057 --> 00:11:15,682
You talking to me, thing?

230
00:11:15,682 --> 00:11:17,493
Someone is very cocky.

231
00:11:18,244 --> 00:11:19,584
Well, I cracked the case.

232
00:11:19,584 --> 00:11:21,875
Caught the guy?

233
00:11:21,875 --> 00:11:23,972
Well, I nicked the case.

234
00:11:23,972 --> 00:11:26,194
Turns out the killer
left a message

235
00:11:26,194 --> 00:11:28,066
and nobody saw it but me.

236
00:11:28,791 --> 00:11:31,155
I'm proud of you, baby.

237
00:11:32,364 --> 00:11:33,154
Are you?

238
00:11:33,154 --> 00:11:34,468
Yeah.

239
00:11:34,468 --> 00:11:36,448
I'm always proud of you.

240
00:11:36,448 --> 00:11:39,564
Whatever else, I am
always proud of you.

241
00:11:40,541 --> 00:11:42,739
Want to hear something funny?

242
00:11:42,739 --> 00:11:45,105
You going to start, start
calling me "toy" again, huh?

243
00:11:46,139 --> 00:11:48,679
You know who showed
me the clue?

244
00:11:48,679 --> 00:11:51,775
Who?
Captain Kenneth Push
of the Texas Rangers.

245
00:11:51,775 --> 00:11:52,875
I don't get it?

246
00:11:52,875 --> 00:11:53,851
What was he doing there?

247
00:11:53,851 --> 00:11:55,558
Well, that's the thing--
he wasn't there,

248
00:11:55,558 --> 00:11:57,222
It was a vision I had.

249
00:12:00,457 --> 00:12:03,705
That's right.
You've haven't met

250
00:12:05,981 --> 00:12:08,550
Trust me, you have
nothing to worry about.

251
00:12:08,550 --> 00:12:10,321
Oh, really?

252
00:12:10,744 --> 00:12:12,382
Are you prepared to prove that?

253
00:12:12,382 --> 00:12:13,555
Maybe.

254
00:12:13,555 --> 00:12:15,329
On your mark.

255
00:12:15,329 --> 00:12:17,026
Get set...

256
00:12:17,026 --> 00:12:18,379
Go!

257
00:12:18,379 --> 00:12:19,256
Hey.

258
00:12:34,737 --> 00:12:35,692
Mom?

259
00:12:36,428 --> 00:12:40,047
Can you still ride
horses in a hurricane?

260
00:12:45,384 --> 00:12:46,955
Aren't there supposed
to be two dice?

261
00:12:46,955 --> 00:12:48,807
What's the difference?
We'll just play with one dice.

262
00:12:48,807 --> 00:12:50,653
I don't think that's gonna
work 'cause you have to move

263
00:12:50,653 --> 00:12:52,003
at least seven paces
for the game to work.

264
00:12:52,003 --> 00:12:53,821
Well, just double
