for Mr. Push sometime
after 3:00 this morning.

523
00:23:59,476 --> 00:24:01,436
They took him over to
St. Christopher's Hospital.

524
00:24:04,890 --> 00:24:07,726
Now, look, Captain
Push, I appreciate
you're far from home

525
00:24:07,801 --> 00:24:09,992
but these temporary
pacemakers are
only designed

526
00:24:09,992 --> 00:24:11,625
to work three or
four days at a time

527
00:24:11,625 --> 00:24:13,879
before a permanent
unit can be placed
inside the body.

528
00:24:13,879 --> 00:24:16,378
It's a pretty straightforward
procedure.

529
00:24:16,378 --> 00:24:18,600
I wish you would reconsider
and let me do it.

530
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:20,324
Doctor...

531
00:24:20,324 --> 00:24:22,920
this is the first time
you and I have met, right?

532
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:27,139
No offense, but...
I'm not in the habit

533
00:24:27,139 --> 00:24:29,548
of letting a perfect stranger
slice me up the middle

534
00:24:29,548 --> 00:24:34,128
and install miniature
electronics in my chest.

535
00:24:34,987 --> 00:24:38,723
Now, I have a wonderful doctor
back home

536
00:24:38,723 --> 00:24:42,628
who knows me inside and out,
and in a day and a half,

537
00:24:42,628 --> 00:24:45,981
when you let me out of this bed,
I'm flying back to Texas,

538
00:24:45,981 --> 00:24:48,569
and I'll have him do
whatever is necessary.

539
00:24:48,569 --> 00:24:50,237
ALLISON:
You causing trouble?

540
00:24:50,237 --> 00:24:51,638
Uh-huh.

541
00:24:56,786 --> 00:24:58,188
You Mrs. Dubois?

542
00:24:58,188 --> 00:25:00,301
Yup. I'm the woman
who fed him

543
00:25:00,301 --> 00:25:01,777
whatever it is that
put him in here.

544
00:25:01,777 --> 00:25:05,227
DOCTOR:
Well, maybe you can convince him
to let me operate,

545
00:25:05,227 --> 00:25:07,017
put in that pacemaker
so he can go back home.

546
00:25:07,017 --> 00:25:09,324
I'm fine.

547
00:25:09,324 --> 00:25:12,619
I got this outboard model
right here.

548
00:25:12,619 --> 00:25:15,557
Tells my heart when to beat,

549
00:25:15,557 --> 00:25:17,636
holds all my addresses
and phone numbers.

550
00:25:17,636 --> 00:25:19,847
I even get AM/FM radio.

551
00:25:19,847 --> 00:25:20,697
DOCTOR:
Yeah.

552
00:25:20,697 --> 00:25:23,719
Well, I'm gonna go ahead
and call your doctor in Houston,

553
00:25:23,719 --> 00:25:27,064
see if he can't convince you.Mrs. Dubois.

554
00:25:28,791 --> 00:25:31,633
(muttering):
He's gonna phone my doctor in Houston...

555
00:25:31,633 --> 00:25:33,160
Oh, boy.

556
00:25:34,216 --> 00:25:36,923
I let you out of my
sight for 20 minutes.

557
00:25:36,923 --> 00:25:39,410
I don't know
what to tell you.

558
00:25:39,410 --> 00:25:42,086
Woke up in the middle
of the night.

559
00:25:42,086 --> 00:25:44,066
Recognized the feeling.

560
00:25:44,066 --> 00:25:47,074
Knew exactly
what was happening.

561
00:25:47,074 --> 00:25:49,700
Called downstairs
to the desk

562
00:25:49,700 --> 00:25:52,964
and must have...
blacked out right after that.

563
00:25:52,964 --> 00:25:56,700
Next thing I know,
they're working on an ambulance.

564
00:25:56,700 --> 00:25:59,846
I'm guessing this
was around 3:30
in the morning.

565
00:25:59,846 --> 00:26:02,386
Yeah. I don't know.

566
00:26:02,386 --> 00:26:03,758
You were wearing
blue boxers

567
00:26:03,758 --> 00:26:05,146
and a white T-shirt.

568
00:26:06,693 --> 00:26:09,445
You gonna guess
my weight now?

569
00:26:09,445 --> 00:26:12,680
I think you came to see me
last night.

570
00:26:14,163 --> 00:26:15,348
Come again?

571
00:26:15,653 --> 00:26:18,139
You came to visit me,
in my bedroom.

572
00:26:18,139 --> 00:26:19,557
It was around 3:30
in the morning.

573
00:26:19,557 --> 00:26:20,876
I thought that I was dreaming.

574
00:26:20,876 --> 00:26:23,090
I didn't know
what was happening.

575
00:26:23,090 --> 00:26:24,186
But now I realize...

576
00:26:25,151 --> 00:26:26,383
it was you.

577
00:26:29,914 --> 00:26:32,337
You must have died
for a minute or two.

578
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:38,197
I know you have a
difficult time with
this kind of thing.

579
00:26:39,126 --> 00:26:41,397
<i>( quietly ):
I don't know what to say.</i>

580
00:26:43,296 --> 00:26:46,443
Showed up in my boxers, huh?

581
00:26:46,443 --> 00:26:48,793
Hope I didn't offend

582
00:26:48,793 --> 00:26:50,359
<i>the other guests.
( laughs )</i>

583
00:26:51,623 --> 00:26:55,527
You said that where you were,
you could see everything,

584
00:26:55,527 --> 00:26:58,040
that you had
this enormous clarity.

585
00:26:59,106 --> 00:27:00,405
Allison...

586
00:27:00,669 --> 00:27:02,511
You were very excited--
you told me that

587
00:27:02,511 --> 00:27:04,154
all the murders were related.

588
00:27:04,154 --> 00:27:07,370
That the victims
weren't random.

589
00:27:07,370 --> 00:27:09,850
Not random, huh?

590
00:27:09,850 --> 00:27:12,817
That hardly seems
like a revelation

591
00:27:12,817 --> 00:27:15,246
worthy of a near-death
experience.

592
00:27:15,246 --> 00:27:18,397
And then you said you knew
who the next victim would be.

593
00:27:20,595 --> 00:27:21,978
And...?

594
00:27:21,978 --> 00:27:23,367
And...

595
00:27:25,892 --> 00:27:28,130
I guess that's when
they brought you back to life.

596
00:27:28,130 --> 00:27:30,511
You never said
their name.

597
00:27:30,511 --> 00:27:32,399
You just disappeared.

598
00:27:32,399 --> 00:27:35,995
Or I fell asleep, or...

599
00:27:37,540 --> 00:27:39,457
I know you well enough to know

600
00:27:39,457 --> 00:27:41,222
that you wouldn't be
telling me these things

601
00:27:41,222 --> 00:27:43,343
if you didn't believe them
with all your heart.

602
00:27:44,759 --> 00:27:47,771
Captain Push...
I have
no recollection

603
00:27:47,771 --> 00:27:50,684
of seeing anyone last night

604
00:27:50,684 --> 00:27:53,535
except a very frightened
hotel manager

605
00:27:53,535 --> 00:27:56,864
and a couple very able EMS guys

606
00:27:56,864 --> 00:28:01,206
whose names I don't remember
and who probably saved my life.

607
00:28:02,379 --> 00:28:04,524
Allison...

608
00:28:04,524 --> 00:28:07,415
I'm a lawman.

609
00:28:09,425 --> 00:28:11,618
This maniac

610
00:28:11,618 --> 00:28:13,782
killed three Texans.

611
00:28:13,782 --> 00:28:15,321
Don't you think

612
00:28:15,321 --> 00:28:16,614
I'd tell you if I knew

613
00:28:16,614 --> 00:28:18,277
what tied all these people
together?

614
00:28:18,277 --> 00:28:20,560
Don't you think I'd tell you

615
00:28:20,560 --> 00:28:23,876
if I knew who he was fixin'
to kill next?

616
00:28:23,876 --> 00:28:25,857
Of course.

617
00:28:27,522 --> 00:28:29,149
Related? How?

618
00:28:29,206 --> 00:28:30,688
You're not giving me
much to work with.

619
00:28:30,688 --> 00:28:32,732
I don't know,
they're just related.

620
00:28:32,732 --> 00:28:35,211
And you came upon this
startling revelation how?

621
00:28:35,954 --> 00:28:37,716
It's not important.

622
00:28:43,316 --> 00:28:45,802
It's Detective
Scanlon. Damn.

623
00:28:45,802 --> 00:28:48,398
It's 2:40. You'll
wake the baby.

624
00:28:48,398 --> 00:28:49,785
Just click it
and hang up.

625
00:28:53,845 --> 00:28:54,782
<i>( over phone ):
Allison...</i>

626
00:28:54,782 --> 00:28:56,258
All right, talk to him.

627
00:28:56,258 --> 00:28:57,558
I'll get the baby.
Hello?

628
00:28:57,558 --> 00:29:00,379
No, it's okay, he understands.
What's going on?

629
00:29:00,379 --> 00:29:02,636
We found the bodies
of Darlene Denise

630
00:29:02,636 --> 00:29:04,191
and, uh, Katie Fisher.

631
00:29:04,191 --> 00:29:06,032
Okay, where did he leave them?

632
00:29:06,954 --> 00:29:09,431
A church. Downtown.

633
00:29:09,431 --> 00:29:11,637
Right in the middle
of Metro district.

634
00:29:11,637 --> 00:29:14,515
Wait a second,
does that fit the pattern?

635
00:29:14,515 --> 00:29:16,241
Well, it's not a nudie bar

636
00:29:16,241 --> 00:29:17,504
and it's not an abortion clinic,

637
00:29:17,504 --> 00:29:19,327
but it's kind of
a nontraditional church.

638
00:29:20,263 --> 00:29:21,457
Female priest.

639
00:29:21,457 --> 00:29:24,555
Gay choir. I mean,
if you're the kind of killer

640
00:29:24,555 --> 00:29:25,974
who likes fire
with his brimstone,

641
00:29:25,974 --> 00:29:27,834
it's probably the kind of place
that would tick you off.

642
00:29:27,834 --> 00:29:29,369
What about Isaiah?

643
00:29:29,369 --> 00:29:32,311
He's here--
every prayerbook in every pew,

644
00:29:32,311 --> 00:29:33,925
there's a bookmark
so you open right to it.

645
00:29:35,157 --> 00:29:37,075
<i>So, you want to come down?
( Marie crying )</i>

646
00:29:37,075 --> 00:29:38,984
I can send a car for you.

647
00:29:39,661 --> 00:29:40,995
It's up to you.

648
00:29:40,995 --> 00:29:43,114
I just thought y you might want
to come down here and,

649
00:29:43,114 --> 00:29:46,123
uh...commune.

650
00:29:46,942 --> 00:29:48,031
You know what?

651
00:29:48,031 --> 00:29:50,234
Let's talk tomorrow.
I'll give you a call.

652
00:29:50,234 --> 00:29:52,397
All right. Absolutely.

653
00:29:52,397 --> 00:29:53,864
'Kay, thanks.

654
00:29:55,085 --> 00:29:56,857
Is it anything
important?

655
00:29:56,857 --> 00:29:58,117
Nah.

656
00:29:58,117 --> 00:29:59,992
Shh... sweetheart.

657
00:30:01,462 --> 00:30:03,781
You're making
the right decision.

658
00:30:03,781 --> 00:30:05,524
Don't gloat.

659
00:30:06,275 --> 00:30:07,988
<i>I'm not making any decision.</i>

660
00:30:07,988 --> 00:30:10,889
You brain-washed
my doctor back home.

661
00:30:17,024 --> 00:30:19,133
Captain Push here.

662
00:30:19,133 --> 00:30:21,005
Allison Dubois here.

663
00:30:22,039 --> 00:30:25,321
Well, you're in
an awfully good mood.

664
00:30:26,242 --> 00:30:28,405
I'll bet that's 'cause
you're not surrounded

665
00:30:28,405 --> 00:30:31,921
by people hell-bent on playing with your innards.

666
00:30:31,921 --> 00:30:34,109
No. But I am staring
at my little baby

667
00:30:34,109 --> 00:30:36,461
who has a bit of a fever--
which is why I'm calling.

668
00:30:36,461 --> 00:30:39,793
I really wanted to stop by and
see you today before you left,

669
00:30:39,793 --> 00:30:41,591
but I just don't know
how I'm gonna do it.

670
00:30:41,591 --> 00:30:45,970
Well, then I have some good news
and I have some bad news.

671
00:30:45,970 --> 00:30:49,752
The good news is,
I'm not leaving quite so fast.

672
00:30:49,827 --> 00:30:53,913
The bad news is,
they're opening up my chest tomorrow morning,

673
00:30:53,913 --> 00:30:57,388
and I may not feel too much
like entertaining after that.

674
00:30:57,388 --> 00:30:58,905
Oh, no.

675
00:30:58,905 --> 00:31:00,860
Well, maybe I could swing by

676
00:31:00,860 --> 00:31:03,790
and see you after
my husband gets home.

677
00:31:04,270 --> 00:31:08,462
Hell, I'll have them dress me
in some fresh gauze

678
00:31:08,462 --> 00:31:09,901
if I know you're coming.

679
00:31:10,690 --> 00:31:12,176
<i>( laughs softly ):
It's a deal.</i>

680
00:31:13,659 --> 00:31:17,010
Captain Push, forgive me,
I'm getting another call.

681
00:31:17,010 --> 00:31:18,910
Give me a second,
I'll get rid of 'em.

682
00:31:20,269 --> 00:31:21,201
Hello?

683
00:31:21,201 --> 00:31:22,947
DEVALOS:
Allison.

684
00:31:22,947 --> 00:31:25,047
Good afternoon, sir.

685
00:31:25,047 --> 00:31:26,401
I have somebody
on the other line.

686
00:31:26,401 --> 00:31:27,697
Let me just...
That's all right,

687
00:31:27,697 --> 00:31:28,879
this'll just take a moment.

688
00:31:28,879 --> 00:31:30,926
Now that we have two bodies,

689
00:31:30,926 --> 00:31:32,541
and based
on our conversation yesterday,

690
00:31:32,541 --> 00:31:35,117
I took a flier and ordered up
some comparative DNA.

691
00:31:35,117 --> 00:31:36,530
Now, I just received

692
00:31:36,530 --> 00:31:38,859
the first report
about 20 minutes ago, and...

693
00:31:38,859 --> 00:31:41,787
<i>( sighs ):
Allison, these two women
are related.</i>

694
00:31:44,574 --> 00:31:45,901
Excuse me?

695
00:31:45,901 --> 00:31:47,971
I haven't figured out how
quite yet,

696
00:31:47,971 --> 00:31:50,212
but according
to their DNA markers,

697
00:31:50,212 --> 00:31:52,615
both women have the same father.

698
00:31:53,752 --> 00:31:56,417
<i>Allison?
( sighs )</i>

699
00:31:56,417 --> 00:31:59,344
I-I'm sorry, I just, uh...

700
00:31:59,344 --> 00:32:01,151
Just thought you'd want to know.

701
00:32:01,151 --> 00:32:02,930
Bye.
Thank you.

702
00:32:02,930 --> 00:32:04,909
Hello? Are you still there?

703
00:32:04,909 --> 00:32:06,906
That is not the kind of thing

704
00:32:06,906 --> 00:32:09,323
you want to be asking
a man in my condition.

705
00:32:10,358 --> 00:32:13,593
Okay, I hear no laughter.

706
00:32:13,593 --> 00:32:15,200
You all right?

707
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:18,669
Yeah. N-No. I just...
That was the office--

708
00:32:18,669 --> 00:32:21,402
they ran some comparative DNA
on our first two victims.

709
00:32:21,402 --> 00:32:24,754
They don't understand how,
but according to the lab,

710
00:32:24,754 --> 00:32:26,948
both of these women
are actually related.

711
00:32:26,948 --> 00:32:30,652
From a genetic standpoint,
they have the same father.

712
00:32:32,398 --> 00:32:35,829
Captain Push?

713
00:33:23,468 --> 00:33:24,935
Hey, everybody.

714
00:33:32,885 --> 00:33:33,905
Hi., Daddy.

715
00:33:33,905 --> 00:33:37,129
Wow, Daddy, who's that for?

716
00:33:38,207 --> 00:33:40,459
The balloon is for Marie,
the wine's for Mommy and me.

717
00:33:40,459 --> 00:33:41,642
Where's everyone?

718
00:33:42,399 --> 00:33:45,185
Marie's sleeping
and Mom's getting dressed.

719
00:33:48,579 --> 00:33:50,556
Hey.

720
00:33:50,556 --> 00:33:53,909
Thank God. I was hoping you'd
show up about 15 minutes ago.

721
00:33:53,909 --> 00:33:56,141
I stopped to pick up
a couple of things.

722
00:33:56,141 --> 00:33:58,098
Are you going somewhere?

723
00:33:58,098 --> 00:33:59,181
Don't be mad.

724
00:33:59,181 --> 00:34:01,679
The Phoenix Phantom snatched
another girl.

725
00:34:01,679 --> 00:34:04,594
Devalos called. He asked me
to stop by the crime scene.

726
00:34:04,594 --> 00:34:06,179
I've been waiting
for you to get home.

727
00:34:06,179 --> 00:34:07,862
I have to stick my head in
at the hospital.

728
00:34:07,862 --> 00:34:09,103
Say hi to Captain Push.

729
00:34:09,103 --> 00:34:10,954
Turns out they're
operating on
him tomorrow

730
00:34:10,954 --> 00:34:11,972
I feel badly--

731
00:34:11,972 --> 00:34:12,998
he's in a strange city.

732
00:34:12,998 --> 00:34:14,504
He doesn't know anybody.

733
00:34:14,504 --> 00:34:18,208
Marie's fever broke hours ago.

734
00:34:18,208 --> 00:34:19,311
She's out like a light.

735
00:34:20,348 --> 00:34:22,603
There's meat loaf in the oven.

736
00:34:22,603 --> 00:34:23,983
It'll be ready in 15 minutes.

737
00:34:23,983 --> 00:34:25,117
There's coleslaw
in the fridge.

738
00:34:25,117 --> 00:34:27,121
So, if I leave
right now

739
00:34:27,121 --> 00:34:29,334
I have a chance
of getting back by 9:30.

740
00:34:29,334 --> 00:34:31,862
You still proud of me?

741
00:34:31,862 --> 00:34:34,622
BRIDGETTE:
Look what
Daddy brought.

742
00:34:37,347 --> 00:34:40,407
Isn't Marie a little young
for this?

743
00:34:40,407 --> 00:34:41,913
Get out of here.

744
00:34:41,913 --> 00:34:44,066
We'll have this fight at 9:30.

745
00:34:44,066 --> 00:34:45,053
You promise?

746
00:34:45,053 --> 00:34:47,481
I'm uncorking that at 9:15.

747
00:34:47,481 --> 00:34:49,004
Shall we synchronize
our watches?

748
00:34:49,004 --> 00:34:50,186
Just go.

749
00:35:16,779 --> 00:35:17,971
PUSH:
Hey.

750
00:35:17,971 --> 00:35:19,786
Hey.

751
00:35:19,786 --> 00:35:22,485
How long you been sitting there?

752
00:35:23,952 --> 00:35:25,262
A bit.

753
00:35:26,797 --> 00:35:29,364
They told me they gave you
a little something

754
00:35:29,364 --> 00:35:31,208
to help take the edge off.

755
00:35:31,208 --> 00:35:35,534
Is that what they call it,
an edge?

756
00:35:37,707 --> 00:35:39,491
For what it's worth,

757
00:35:39,491 --> 00:35:42,998
apparently this is a fairly
run-of-the-mill operation.

758
00:35:42,998 --> 00:35:44,800
It's not about my heart.

759
00:35:47,491 --> 00:35:51,390
I could have stopped this thing.

760
00:35:51,390 --> 00:35:53,306
You don't know that.

761
00:35:53,306 --> 00:35:57,239
Yeah, I do.

762
00:35:58,318 --> 00:36:02,582
Called Texas right after
you and I got off the phone.

763
00:36:03,806 --> 00:36:05,921
Had them pull out
the old lab work.

764
00:36:05,921 --> 00:36:09,172
It was there all along.

765
00:36:09,172 --> 00:36:10,807
Just never
looked for it.

766
00:36:12,107 --> 00:36:13,721
You told me.

767
00:36:13,721 --> 00:36:16,857
You said, they're related--

768
00:36:16,857 --> 00:36:19,013
and they were.

769
00:36:19,013 --> 00:36:22,681
No, Captain Push.
You told me.

770
00:36:24,398 --> 00:36:28,332
I can't remember
the person's name.

771
00:36:29,021 --> 00:36:32,510
I've been thinking...

772
00:36:32,510 --> 00:36:35,452
I've been trying all day.

773
00:36:35,452 --> 00:36:37,764
The next victim.

774
00:36:37,764 --> 00:36:41,538
You told me I...
I tried to tell you.

775
00:36:44,574 --> 00:36:47,053
What time is it?

776
00:36:47,053 --> 00:36:49,599
I lost all track of time.

777
00:36:49,599 --> 00:36:51,264
It's 10:15.

